Description: Age Bracket Verification Daemon
 aged is a daemon that stores a user's birthdate, defines
 jurisdiction-specific age brackets, and exposes a D-Bus (and CLI)
 API for applications to query which bracket the user falls into.
 .
 Jurisdictions such as US/California and US/Colorado define their
 own age brackets. The daemon stores the birthdate in the user's
 keychain via the Secret Service API, falling back to a plain file.
